==== Lucky Seven Skills ==== When [[Noah]] uses [[Unlimited Sword]], the skills belonging to his current class, along with any equipped skills, do not have any effect, and are replaced by a new set of skills for 90 seconds, or until Noah is incapacitated. The effect of these skills varies, depending on Noah's current [[Role]].
{| class="xc1" style="" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1" border="0" ! scope="col" style="width: 80px;" |Role ! scope="col" style="width: 500px;" |Skills |- |rowspan="4" style="text-align:center;"|[[File:XC3 Attacker Role Icon.png|40px|center]][[Attacker]] |3% chance to inflict [[Doom (XC3)|Doom]] on an enemy (excluding bosses/uniques). |- |Boosts damage dealt by 10% and Critical Rate by 6% on critical hit (up to a maximum of 200% for both). |- |On critical hit, recharge Art used by 20%. |- |Reduces aggro generated from attacks by 40%. |- |rowspan="4" style="text-align:center;"|[[File:XC3 Defender Role Icon.png|40px|center]]{{Link noparens|Defender (XC3)}} |Boosts evasion by 2% when you take damage (up to a maximum of 50%). |- |Deals 200% of Attack damage when you evade an attack. |- |Reduces damage taken by allies in a fixed radius by 30%. |- |Accrues Aggro every second and increases aggro generated by 30%. |- |rowspan="4" style="text-align:center;"|[[File:XC3 Healer Role Icon.png|40px|center]] [[Healer]] |Boosts damage by 10% upon healing an ally (up to a maximum of 100%). |- |Deal 100% more damage and take 25% less damage when an ally is down/has low HP. |- |Grants [[Invincible (XC3)|Invincible]] to revived allies. |- |Reduces aggro generated from attacks by 40%. |}
=== Master Skills === Once a Character has ranked up a Class, the controlled characters can use certain Arts from that class even if they change to another Class. This is called a '''Master Skill'''. For example, if Noah uses the Tactician class, he will be able to use some of that class' Skills even if he changes back to [[Swordfighter]]. Unlike [[Battle Arts (XC3)|Master Arts]], Skills can be equipped regardless of the class' affiliation with [[Keves]] or [[Agnus]].
Upon reaching Rank 5 in a class, one of the Master Skills will be unlocked. The second Master Skill is unlocked at Rank 15.
Each character has 3 Master Skill slots available to them, with the first being accessible by default, the second unlocking at [[Level (XC3)|level]] 30, and the third unlocking at level 50.
The [[Soulhacker]] class cannot use Master Skills, and the only Master Skill from the class is Soul Hack, which is unlocked at Rank 10.
